  "text": "Second, a reinforcement-like process may cause cryptic reproductive isolation via selection against maladaptive hybridization (Coyne & Orr 2004) . Under this scenario, greater divergence is expected between populations in geographical contact versus geographically separated populations, because maladaptive hybridization occurs only in the former situation [CITATION_1] .",
